sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway<br/>(Envoy)
    participant EPP as llm-d-inference-scheduler<br/>(EPP ext_proc)
    participant Prefill as vLLM Prefill Pod
    participant Sidecar as llm-d-routing-sidecar
    participant KVCache as KV Cache<br/>(NIXL / shared storage)
    participant Decode as vLLM Decode Pod
    participant WVA as Workload Variant<br/>Autoscaler

    Note over Client,WVA: Workflow 4: LLM Inference with Disaggregated P/D (llm-d)

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>(OpenAI-compatible, HTTPS/443)

    Gateway->>EPP: ext_proc filter invocation<br/>(gRPC)
    EPP->>EPP: Score endpoints:<br/>- KV cache prefix match<br/>- Queue depth<br/>- LoRA adapter availability
    EPP-->>Gateway: Target headers<br/>(selected prefill pod)

    Gateway->>Prefill: Route request to<br/>prefill pod (mTLS)
    Prefill->>Prefill: Execute prefill phase<br/>(compute KV cache for prompt)

    Prefill->>KVCache: Transfer KV cache<br/>(NIXL V2 protocol)
    Prefill->>Sidecar: Signal prefill complete

    Sidecar->>Sidecar: Coordinate decode handoff
    Sidecar->>Decode: Route to decode pod<br/>with KV cache ref

    Decode->>KVCache: Load KV cache
    loop Token generation
        Decode->>Decode: Generate next token
        Decode-->>Client: SSE stream token<br/>(Server-Sent Events)
    end

    Decode-->>Client: Stream complete<br/>(final response)

    Note over WVA,EPP: Background: Traffic-aware autoscaling

    WVA->>EPP: Scrape EPP metrics<br/>(queue depth, latency)
    WVA->>WVA: Evaluate scaling policy<br/>per InferencePool
    WVA->>WVA: Scale prefill/decode pools<br/>independently via HPA
